President Obama and First Lady Michelle Obama expressed their sadness upon learning of the passing of Pastor Andrae Crouch. They highlighted his extraordinary musical talent and his influential career that spanned over 50 years. Pastor Crouch was a leading pioneer of contemporary gospel music, and his soulful classics uplifted the hearts and minds of several generations. The Obamas expressed gratitude that his music and spirit will continue to live on for years to come and extended their thoughts and prayers to his family, friends, and fans.